When I started out tattooing, painting used to stress me out and frustrate me. I hated it cause I wanted to be good but i sucked. 
  But I kept at it. Painting and painting and painting more. Trying new things. Figuring out what materials worked best for me. And just kept painting more and more and more. 
  And while I’m always going to strive to get better, now, years later, i LOVE to paint. It relaxes me. It puts me at ease. It calms my mind and erases all life’s distractions and stressors and for however long i am painting, it’s just me the brush and the paper and nothing else. 
 Bla bla bla, moral of the story is this: if you have the passion in you, there’s a path to get to where you want to be.  If the passion is there you’ll work hard at getting to where you want to be and next thing you know you’ll be reflecting back on your journey and be glad you had put in the time and effort to be able to achieve your goals and aspirations. 
  You’ll be the only person who’ll be able to get in your way. Don’t let self doubt stop you from going after something you want for yourself. Believe in yourself. You’ll get there. #painting #paintingvideo #watercolorvideo #paintingprocess #watercolorprocess #tattooflash #tattooing #traditionalflash #pinwheelflower #traditionalflower
